  "text": "The Kubernetes CronJob API migration from v1beta1 to batch/v1 is implemented across multiple layers in the kubernetes/kubernetes repository:\n\n## API Type Definitions\n\n**v1 API** (staging/src/k8s.io/api/batch/v1/types.go): Defines the current stable CronJob type with:\n- CronJob struct with metadata, spec, and status\n- CronJobSpec containing Schedule (string), TimeZone (*string), StartingDeadlineSeconds, ConcurrencyPolicy, Suspend, JobTemplate, and history limits\n- CronJobStatus with Active, LastScheduleTime, and LastSuccessfulTime fields\n- CronJobList for list responses\n- TimeZone field introduced at line 748 as optional, supporting IANA time zone database names\n\n**v1beta1 API** (staging/src/k8s.io/api/batch/v1beta1/types.go): The deprecated beta version marked with:\n- +k8s:prerelease-lifecycle-gen:deprecated=1.21\n- +k8s:prerelease-lifecycle-gen:removed=1.25\n- +k8s:prerelease-lifecycle-gen:replacement=batch,v1,CronJob\n- Contains identical TimeZone field (line 99) as v1, indicating the field was added early in the beta lifecycle\n\n**Internal API** (pkg/apis/batch/types.go): Defines the canonical internal types used by the API server internally, also containing CronJob, CronJobSpec, CronJobStatus with TimeZone support.\n\n## Version Conversion Functions\n\n**v1 Conversions** (pkg/apis/batch/v1/zz_generated.conversion.go):\n- Convert_v1_CronJob_To_batch_CronJob and Convert_batch_CronJob_To_v1_CronJob for full object conversion\n- Convert_v1_CronJobSpec_To_batch_CronJobSpec and Convert_batch_CronJobSpec_To_v1_CronJobSpec for spec conversion\n- Convert_v1_CronJobStatus_To_batch_CronJobStatus and Convert_batch_CronJobStatus_To_v1_CronJobStatus for status conversion\n- TimeZone field conversion uses: `out.TimeZone = (*string)(unsafe.Pointer(in.TimeZone))` to safely convert pointers\n\n**v1beta1 Conversions** (pkg/apis/batch/v1beta1/zz_generated.conversion.go):\n- Parallel conversion functions: Convert_v1beta1_CronJob_To_batch_CronJob, Convert_batch_CronJob_To_v1beta1_CronJob\n- Convert_v1beta1_CronJobSpec_To_batch_CronJobSpec and Convert_batch_CronJobSpec_To_v1beta1_CronJobSpec\n- Convert_v1beta1_CronJobStatus_To_batch_CronJobStatus and Convert_batch_CronJobStatus_To_v1beta1_CronJobStatus\n- Identical TimeZone field conversion pattern as v1\n\n**Conversion Setup** (pkg/apis/batch/v1/conversion.go and v1beta1/conversion.go):\n- Field label conversion functions for selectable metadata fields\n- Both versions support querying by metadata.name, metadata.namespace, and status.successful\n\n## Defaulting Logic Differences\n\n**v1 Defaults** (pkg/apis/batch/v1/defaults.go):\n- SetDefaults_CronJob function defaults:\n  - ConcurrencyPolicy to AllowConcurrent if empty\n  - Suspend to false if nil\n  - SuccessfulJobsHistoryLimit to 3 if nil\n  - FailedJobsHistoryLimit to 1 if nil\n- Uses modern ptr.To() utility functions for creating pointers\n\n**v1beta1 Defaults** (pkg/apis/batch/v1beta1/defaults.go):\n- SetDefaults_CronJob function with identical defaults:\n  - ConcurrencyPolicy to AllowConcurrent\n  - Suspend, SuccessfulJobsHistoryLimit (3), and FailedJobsHistoryLimit (1)\n- Uses legacy raw new() pointers and manual dereference pattern instead of ptr.To()\n\n**Auto-generated Defaults** (pkg/apis/batch/v1/zz_generated.defaults.go and v1beta1/zz_generated.defaults.go):\n- Additional auto-generated defaulting for JobTemplateSpec and other nested fields\n\n## Validation Logic\n\n**CronJob Validation** (pkg/apis/batch/validation/validation.go):\n- ValidateCronJobCreate: Creates validation including metadata name length check (must be <= 52 chars due to 11-char suffix added by controller)\n- ValidateCronJobUpdate: Updates validation with allowance for old CronJobs with longer names\n- validateCronJobSpec: Validates the spec with special handling for TimeZone changes\n  - Validates schedule format using cron/v3 parser\n  - Enforces constraint that both TZ in schedule AND timeZone field cannot be used simultaneously\n  - Only validates TimeZone field changes (not on creation if unchanged from update)\n\n**TimeZone Validation** (validateTimeZone function):\n- Rejects nil or empty TimeZone strings\n- Validates IANA time zone naming convention using regex: `^[A-Za-z\\\\.\\-_0-9+]{1,14}$`\n- Prevents '.' and '..' directory components\n- Prevents components starting with '-'\n- Disallows legacy 'Local' time zone name (must be explicit IANA zone)\n- Verifies time zone can be loaded with time.LoadLocation()\n\n**Schedule Format Validation** (validateScheduleFormat function):\n- Validates cron expression format using cron.ParseStandard()\n- Enforces migration from TZ variable in schedule to timeZone field:\n  - Allows TZ in schedule only if oldSpec already had it (backward compatibility)\n  - Otherwise requires timeZone field instead of TZ/CRON_TZ in schedule\n\n## Storage and Strategy\n\n**CronJob Strategy** (pkg/registry/batch/cronjob/strategy.go):\n- cronJobStrategy implements creation/update validation and preparation\n- PrepareForCreate clears status, sets generation to 1\n- PrepareForUpdate preserves status, increments generation on spec changes\n- ValidateCronJob delegates to batchvalidation.ValidateCronJobCreate/Update\n- DefaultGarbageCollectionPolicy differs by version: OrphanDependents for v1beta1 (backward compat), DeleteDependents for v1\n- WarningsOnUpdate warns if TZ variable used in schedule instead of timeZone field (line 159-161)\n\nThe TimeZone field represents a key addition to the CronJob v1 specification, allowing explicit timezone support throughout the API, validation, and controller logic, while v1beta1 maintains backward compatibility with legacy patterns."
